README:
# Courtois-NeuroMod: [harrypotter subdataset](https://github.com/courtois-neuromod/harrypotter) The [Courtois project on Neural Modelling (Courtois NeuroMod)](https://www.cneuromod.ca/) aims at training artificial neural networks using extensive experimental data on individual human brain activity and behaviour. Participants read a chapter of Harry-Potter word-by-word at a 2Hz pace, while functional data being acquired in the MRI scanner. A extensive description can be found [here](https://docs.cneuromod.ca/en/latest/DATASETS.html#harrypotter). This subdataset is organized following the [brain imaging data structure (BIDS)](https://bids.neuroimaging.io/) (including extensions in development) and contains: - [x] [raw neuroimaging data](https://docs.cneuromod.ca/en/latest/MRI.html#functional-sequences) - [x] behavioral variables in event files - [x] physiological data - [x] ECG - [x] pulse (photoplethysmography) - [x] respiration - [x] skin conductance (electro-dermal activity) *(unchecked are collected data which have not yet been integrated in the dataset)* Courtois NeuroMod data are [freely shared with the scientific community](https://docs.cneuromod.ca/en/latest/ACCESS.html) to advance research at the interface of neuroscience and artificial intelligence. Access to to the data is based on a registered access model, see the Courtois NeuroMod website for more information. Redistribution of data outside of the Courtois NeuroMod data bank is prohibited. ## Contributors
